CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. A2 reads: "Key Clubs - The Key Club, a junior service organization affiliated with the Kiwanis Club, last week-end attended the Pennsylvania district convention held in Hilton Hotel, Pittsburgh. Over 1,250 boys were assembled to learn new techniques and projects for the Key Clubs which they represent.  Left photo [right photo] (left to right): Teal Dugan, Lewiston; Ray Queenhan, Ambler, John Miller, Coraopolis; Charles Green, Milton, who are registering for the house delegates' session..
TitMainTitle: Group of Key Club members, from left: Teal Dugan, Ray Queenhan, John Miller, and Charles Green, standing behind table in Hilton Hotel
